00:30:31.280 --> 00:30:33.576
joining us from
the 14th Signal Regiment

495
00:30:33.600 --> 00:30:36.456
and our new Director
of Rapid Reaction.

496
00:30:36.480 --> 00:30:39.536
Lieutenant Colonel Cavendish.
Roz. please.

497
00:30:39.560 --> 00:30:41.096
Thank you. Danny.

498
00:30:41.120 --> 00:30:43.016
Er. first. the uniforms.

499
00:30:43.040 --> 00:30:45.736
Don't worry.
Everyone gets it wrong first day.

500
00:30:45.760 --> 00:30:47.536
CHUCKLES

501
00:30:47.560 --> 00:30:51.296
Yeah. I appreciate there's
a cultural difference here.

502
00:30:51.320 --> 00:30:53.480
You like to listen.
when you're not interrupting.

503
00:30:55.240 --> 00:30:57.336
We like to act.

504
00:30:57.360 --> 00:31:02.216
Hopefully. listening and acting
do not prove mutually exclusive.

505
00:31:02.240 --> 00:31:03.560
And the uniforms stay.

506
00:31:06.800 --> 00:31:07.920
As you were. troops.

507
00:31:10.920 --> 00:31:13.840
Max. Charlie Francis
from Security would like a word.

508
00:31:23.040 --> 00:31:25.576
OK. OK. let's crack on. shall we?
We've got a whole

509
00:31:25.600 --> 00:31:27.776
computer network to analyse
for vulnerabilities

510
00:31:27.800 --> 00:31:32.256
and damage and anything our Russian
visitors may have left behind.

511
00:31:32.280 --> 00:31:33.360
Let's have a good one.

512
00:31:47.040 --> 00:31:50.936
Just a routine security sift. Max.

513
00:31:50.960 --> 00:31:52.016
Given the scare.

514
00:31:52.040 --> 00:31:55.256
those on high are jumpy
and have asked me to check

515
00:31:55.280 --> 00:31:59.120
that all security protocols
have been. and are being. followed.

516
00:32:00.440 --> 00:32:05.256
OK. No bother. Like all teams.
you run a hot-desk policy?

517
00:32:05.280 --> 00:32:08.536
All your programmers can log
in on any computer? Mm-hm.

518
00:32:08.560 --> 00:32:12.816
This applies to all machines.
sandboxes included?

519
00:32:12.840 --> 00:32:14.040
Yeah.

520
00:32:15.440 --> 00:32:17.160
What happens
if you need to leave your desk?

521
00:32:19.080 --> 00:32:20.360
Well. then you log out.

522
00:32:22.280 --> 00:32:25.656
We're. uh. we're pretty hot on that.
Even for a quick pee?

523
00:32:25.680 --> 00:32:27.496
You leave a machine logged in.

524
00:32:27.520 --> 00:32:30.280
and someone comes along
and doesn't know...

525
00:32:31.520 --> 00:32:35.096
accidentally wipes all your work.
Mmm. Or. you know.

526
00:32:35.120 --> 00:32:39.680
spills coffee. whatever. So if
someone. while they're logged in...

527
00:32:40.800 --> 00:32:42.120
accessed something...

528
00:32:43.920 --> 00:32:46.136
Like what? Anything.

529
00:32:46.160 --> 00:32:47.856
Something on the system.

530
00:32:47.880 --> 00:32:50.816
It would pretty much have
to be through their own log-in?

531
00:32:50.840 --> 00:32:53.720
Yes. I'd have thought so.
Can you be 100% sure?

532
00:32:55.040 --> 00:32:57.840
Well. no. but... 99%.

533
00:33:00.040 --> 00:33:01.096
Is this about the attack?

534
00:33:01.120 --> 00:33:02.680
Just answer the questions. please.

535
00:33:11.560 --> 00:33:13.120
PHONE RINGS

536
00:33:19.400 --> 00:33:21.736
Alex. Danny. We've got the sign-off

537
00:33:21.760 --> 00:33:24.296
from Marston on
the Vadim Trusov exfiltration.

538
00:33:24.320 --> 00:33:25.576
That's good.

539
00:33:25.600 --> 00:33:29.136
But. I'm afraid we've had word from
Dutch intel.

540
00:33:29.160 --> 00:33:32.616
They've had a sighting of Trusov.
They've got a hack on the camera on

541
00:33:32.640 --> 00:33:34.616
the FSB entrance
in Saint Petersburg.

542
00:33:34.640 --> 00:33:39.536
It's not good news.
Needless to say. if they have him.

543
00:33:39.560 --> 00:33:44.856
we can't proceed. and I imagine
Vadim Trusov is in grave danger.

544
00:33:44.880 --> 00:33:47.056
Does that mean they know
we're inside their system?

545
00:33:47.080 --> 00:33:48.416
There's no indication as yet.

546
00:33:48.440 --> 00:33:53.456
But if the FSB have got him.
it can only be a matter of time.

547
00:33:53.480 --> 00:33:54.520
OK.

548
00:34:13.680 --> 00:34:15.696
Where are they? Where's who?

549
00:34:15.720 --> 00:34:19.016
The soldiers in the FSB system.
I mean. this is all us.

550
00:34:19.040 --> 00:34:22.016
What are they doing?
They're soldiers.

551
00:34:22.040 --> 00:34:25.096
They follow orders.
They don't ask questions.

552
00:34:25.120 --> 00:34:26.840
Maybe you should try it sometime.

553
00:34:28.240 --> 00:34:29.960
Right after my next sarcasm lesson?

554
00:35:19.520 --> 00:35:20.960
Looking for something?

555
00:35:25.160 --> 00:35:27.096
They're rigging the FSB
system to blow it up.

556
00:35:27.120 --> 00:35:29.056
Excuse me. If we blow the system.

557
00:35:29.080 --> 00:35:31.296
they'll find out how we got in
and trace it back to Vadim.

558
00:35:31.320 --> 00:35:33.600
Saara. go back to your station.
Shall we?

559
00:35:51.480 --> 00:35:52.640
Come in. Danny.

560
00:35:58.800 --> 00:36:00.336
Lieutenant Colonel Cavendish.

561
00:36:00.360 --> 00:36:02.760
I'm so sorry I wasn't
able to greet you earlier.

562
00:36:05.240 --> 00:36:06.896
Problem?

563
00:36:06.920 --> 00:36:08.816
I am the Director of Operations.

564
00:36:08.840 --> 00:36:11.856
I answer to the Foreign Secretary.
I cannot answer to him

565
00:36:11.880 --> 00:36:14.976
if there are operations being
conducted behind my back.

566
00:36:15.000 --> 00:36:16.896
My operation was ordered by
the Foreign Secretary.

567
00:36:16.920 --> 00:36:20.136
It has not been conducted
behind your back. but in parallel.

568
00:36:20.160 --> 00:36:21.176
Operation?

569
00:36:21.200 --> 00:36:25.616
To mine and blow up the FSB system.
and the Russians will retaliate.

570
00:36:25.640 --> 00:36:27.256
It will end in World War III.

571
00:36:27.280 --> 00:36:30.296
To install a comprehensive
array of degrading effects

572
00:36:30.320 --> 00:36:33.536
to trigger as and when we receive
orders from our superiors.

573
00:36:33.560 --> 00:36:37.576
We cannot have two chains of command
in the one operations room.

574
00:36:37.600 --> 00:36:39.016
We don't.

575
00:36:39.040 --> 00:36:42.776
We have two parallel operations.

576
00:36:42.800 --> 00:36:45.960
Our political masters will decide
which one they wish to pursue.

577
00:36:48.880 --> 00:36:50.760
In that case. I'll get back to
what I was doing.

578
00:36:52.240 --> 00:36:53.920
DOOR OPENS Danny. a moment.

579
00:36:59.760 --> 00:37:02.576
I don't like it either but we cannot
control the Government.

580
00:37:02.600 --> 00:37:04.136
We can only advise.

581
00:37:04.160 --> 00:37:07.136
After the last few weeks.
Marston's going to be all over us.

582
00:37:07.160 --> 00:37:08.976
You heard him.

583
00:37:09.000 --> 00:37:11.320
We need to be seen to be running
a steady ship.

584
00:37:15.160 --> 00:37:16.880
And we need to find that mole.

585
00:37:29.000 --> 00:37:32.016
Sally. can you get me Michaela Jones
at the NSA. please?

586
00:37:32.040 --> 00:37:33.040
Of course.

587
00:37:36.600 --> 00:37:38.096
You're gonna let her do it.
aren't you? Sorry.

588
00:37:38.120 --> 00:37:39.376
What about Vadim?

589
00:37:39.400 --> 00:37:41.416
It won't take them long
to work out how we got in.

590
00:37:41.440 --> 00:37:44.576
They're not going to blow it up.
Not if I can help it.

591
00:37:44.600 --> 00:37:47.496
But the news on Vadim is. um...

592
00:37:47.520 --> 00:37:49.536
It's not so good. I'm afraid.

593
00:37:49.560 --> 00:37:52.816
Hacked CCTV footage shows Vadim
and other coders being led out of

594
00:37:52.840 --> 00:37:54.856
the FSB headquarters
in St Petersburg.

595
00:37:54.880 --> 00:37:57.200
When? Same night he leaked
us the material.

596
00:37:58.480 --> 00:37:59.520
That's days ago.

597
00:38:07.360 --> 00:38:09.320
He's only there
because he helped us.

598
00:38:11.160 --> 00:38:12.816
What will they be doing to him?

599
00:38:12.840 --> 00:38:15.616
I don't know. Saara.
I don't know.

600
00:38:15.640 --> 00:38:16.856
MI6 believe that as long

601
00:38:16.880 --> 00:38:18.896
as Vadim is in the hands
of the Russian authorities...

602
00:38:18.920 --> 00:38:21.680
They need to get him out.
They won't be able to help him.

603
00:38:23.240 --> 00:38:24.280
I'm sorry. Saara.

604
00:38:26.880 --> 00:38:27.960
This is all my fault.

605
00:38:45.560 --> 00:38:48.096
That's Michaela for you.
Thank you. Sally.

606
00:38:48.120 --> 00:38:49.976
Michaela. Dan.

607
00:38:50.000 --> 00:38:52.000
We have a problem with
Richard Marston.

608
00:38:53.120 --> 00:38:54.736
He's been moved to Foreign.
hasn't he?

609
00:38:54.760 --> 00:38:57.056
Yeah. He's playing nice.
as nice as he can.

610
00:38:57.080 --> 00:39:00.696
But he's determined to live out his
Churchillian fantasies.

611
00:39:00.720 --> 00:39:04.336
So he's sent in his own dirty tricks
team to blow up the FSB system.

612
00:39:04.360 --> 00:39:07.616
Ah. shit. Greatest listening
opportunity we've ever had

613
00:39:07.640 --> 00:39:10.616
and he wants to piss it up the wall
for the sake of his own ego.

614
00:39:10.640 --> 00:39:12.656
How soon before
his finger gets itchy?

615
00:39:12.680 --> 00:39:15.280
Mmm. I don't know.
but my guess is not long.

616
00:39:17.000 --> 00:39:18.720
I'll talk to Perez. Thank you.

617
00:39:47.920 --> 00:39:51.096
I'd like to work on the
offensive cyber with you.

618
00:39:51.120 --> 00:39:53.056
I don't want to imagine
what they're doing to Vadim.

619
00:39:53.080 --> 00:39:54.600
I just want to hurt them back.

620
00:39:55.840 --> 00:39:57.040
I'm good at this.

621
00:40:03.200 --> 00:40:04.560
Yeah. start on the comms code.

622
00:40:06.080 --> 00:40:07.600
Then... we'll see.

623
00:40:09.120 --> 00:40:10.360
I'll be watching.

624
00:40:46.400 --> 00:40:48.256
KNOCK AT DOOR Come in.

625
00:40:48.280 --> 00:40:49.280
DOOR OPENS

626
00:40:53.200 --> 00:40:55.456
You're working with them now.
are you?

627
00:40:55.480 --> 00:40:56.896
You told me to look

628
00:40:56.920 --> 00:41:00.256
for our missing Mac log-in data
in the FSB system.

629
00:41:00.280 --> 00:41:02.256
Otherwise she'd see me in there.

630
00:41:02.280 --> 00:41:03.816
I'm impressed.

631
00:41:03.840 --> 00:41:05.496
And?

632
00:41:05.520 --> 00:41:08.296
Nothing. Not even a trace.
And there's no sign

633
00:41:08.320 --> 00:41:10.936
of any data they stole
from us in their system.

634
00:41:10.960 --> 00:41:13.480
NOTIFICATION CHIME
Sorry. Saara. I've got to take this.

635
00:41:14.800 --> 00:41:16.776
HE CLEARS THROAT

636
00:41:16.800 --> 00:41:18.200
General Perez. sir.

637
00:41:20.240 --> 00:41:21.336
You have two minutes.

638
00:41:21.360 --> 00:41:23.136
I appreciate I'm speaking out
of turn.

639
00:41:23.160 --> 00:41:26.016
but I felt you should
know our listening operation against

640
00:41:26.040 --> 00:41:29.240
the FSB is in danger.
and not from the Russians.

641
00:41:32.600 --> 00:41:34.080
Night. Dave. See you.

642
00:41:47.080 --> 00:41:48.280
PHONE NOTIFICATION CHIME

643
00:41:57.360 --> 00:41:58.360
Pub?

644
00:42:00.000 --> 00:42:02.040
Thanks. I don't really do pubs.

645
00:42:10.760 --> 00:42:13.176
So. what did old
Checkpoint Charlie want?

646
00:42:13.200 --> 00:42:14.896
Just routine. he said.

647
00:42:14.920 --> 00:42:17.456
But he was asking a lot of questions
about our sandboxes.

648
00:42:17.480 --> 00:42:20.376
Really? Phil? Changed your mind?

649
00:42:20.400 --> 00:42:23.176
Do you know a game called
End of Daze?

650
00:42:23.200 --> 00:42:28.336
Yeah. it's. uh... Horizon Zero Dawn
with a touch of Zelda.

651
00:42:28.360 --> 00:42:30.936
Phil's Mr Gamer.
The rougher the dystopia.

652
00:42:30.960 --> 00:42:32.496
the more he enjoys it.

653
00:42:32.520 --> 00:42:34.840
I just need to know how to get into
the Discord chat.

654
00:42:36.160 --> 00:42:38.320
Well... You'll be sorry you asked.

655
00:42:40.280 --> 00:42:42.296
Let's see.

656
00:42:42.320 --> 00:42:45.896
Yeah.
You need to switch those around.

657
00:42:45.920 --> 00:42:50.456
I swear. if one of
you ever goes behind my back to

658
00:42:50.480 --> 00:42:51.856
the Yanks like that again.

659
00:42:51.880 --> 00:42:54.560
I will see to it
that you're charged with treason.

660
00:42:57.520 --> 00:43:00.776
If I may. Foreign Secretary.
to function effectively

661
00:43:00.800 --> 00:43:04.176
as a government
intelligence gathering institution.

662
00:43:04.200 --> 00:43:07.136
there can be no going
behind anyone's back.

663
00:43:07.160 --> 00:43:09.696
I had hoped this could be a new
beginning.

664
00:43:09.720 --> 00:43:13.960
He means that we understand fully
and unequivocally.

665
00:43:16.640 --> 00:43:17.936
Just to be clear.

666
00:43:17.960 --> 00:43:21.456
we're not triggering the degrading
effects.

667
00:43:21.480 --> 00:43:24.880
That is correct. Lieutenant Colonel.
we are not triggering them...

668
00:43:26.680 --> 00:43:27.840
yet.

669
00:43:45.840 --> 00:43:47.840
How are the interviews going?

670
00:43:48.920 --> 00:43:50.080
Nothing jumping out.

671
00:43:51.640 --> 00:43:54.456
They're a pretty clean bunch.
your coders.

672
00:43:54.480 --> 00:43:57.000
They just busted their guts
turning this thing around.

673
00:43:58.080 --> 00:43:59.640
For one of them to be
the cause of it...

674
00:44:01.360 --> 00:44:03.040
oh. man.
that'd just break my heart.

675
00:44:04.400 --> 00:44:05.440
I pity them.

676
00:44:07.280 --> 00:44:09.056
Nobody wakes up in the morning
and says.

677
00:44:09.080 --> 00:44:10.696
"Today I'm going to betray"

678
00:44:10.720 --> 00:44:14.400
"my colleagues.
my friends. my family. my country."

679
00:44:15.760 --> 00:44:17.736
Sometimes they're believers.

680
00:44:17.760 --> 00:44:19.360
but usually they've been got to.

681
00:44:21.360 --> 00:44:24.040
Love. sex. blackmail.

682
00:44:25.640 --> 00:44:28.800
By the time we get to them. they're
in the worst place in the world.

683
00:44:30.320 --> 00:44:32.680
But don't worry. Dan.
We'll find the mole.

684
00:44:34.960 --> 00:44:36.240
Clock's ticking.

685
00:45:51.160 --> 00:45:52.480
TYPING

686
00:46:49.440 --> 00:46:50.680
What are you doing?

